Ideally, as per web development standards, you shouldn&#39;t have horizontal scrolls on your webpages as this is considered as bad practice.

But still for any specific case you want to do it then you can use style `position:fixed` to do it.

HTML:

    &lt;nav class=&quot;fixedbar&quot;&gt;
        ...
    &lt;/nav&gt;
    

CSS:

    .fixedbar {
         position: fixed;
    }

Or using inline CSS:

HTML:

    &lt;nav style=&quot;position: fixed&quot;&gt;
        ...
    &lt;/nav&gt;

You can achieve it by giving the custom `class` - `increaseFont` to the specific button and override the `font-size` and `color` property.

**View.xml**

    &lt;FlexBox
    	alignItems=&quot;Center&quot;
    	justifyContent=&quot;Start&quot;&gt;
    	&lt;items&gt;
    		&lt;Button enabled=&quot;true&quot; icon=&quot;sap-icon://process&quot; class=&quot;sapUiSmallMarginEnd increaseFont&quot;/&gt;				
    	    &lt;Button enabled=&quot;true&quot; icon=&quot;sap-icon://open-command-field&quot; class=&quot;sapUiSmallMarginEnd&quot;/&gt;
    	    &lt;Button enabled=&quot;true&quot; icon=&quot;sap-icon://navigation-right-arrow&quot; /&gt;		        
    	&lt;/items&gt;
    &lt;/FlexBox&gt;

**CSS**

    .sapMBtn.increaseFont .sapMBtnIcon {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: red;
    }

**Output**

[![enter image description here][1]][1]

Note: All the icons will have the same size. As there are multiple right arrows thats why it look like smaller.


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/5peJ2.png

